    {
        "id": "ec_prepare_fn",
        "type": "function",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "Prepare MQTT Update",
        "func": "// Target entity slug - change this to match your entity\nvar slug = 'gallery-light-1';\n\n// Set MQTT topic for state merge update\nmsg.topic = 'maestra/entity/state/update/' + slug;\n\n// Wrap payload in the expected envelope\nmsg.payload = JSON.stringify({\n    state: msg.payload,\n    source: 'nodered'\n});\n\nreturn msg;",
        "outputs": 1,
        "timeout": "",
        "noerr": 0,
        "initialize": "",
        "finalize": "",
        "libs": [],
        "x": 430,
        "y": 200,
        "wires": [
            ["ec_mqtt_out"]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "ec_mqtt_out",
        "type": "mqtt out",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "Publish State Update",
        "topic": "",
        "qos": "1",
        "retain": "",
        "respTopic": "",
        "contentType": "application/json",
        "userProps": "",
        "correl": "",
        "expiry": "",
        "broker": "mqtt_broker_config",
        "x": 660,
        "y": 200,
        "wires": []
    },
    {
        "id": "ec_mqtt_state",
        "type": "mqtt in",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "All Entity State Broadcasts",
        "topic": "maestra/entity/state/+/+",
        "qos": "0",
        "datatype": "auto",
        "broker": "mqtt_broker_config",
        "nl": false,
        "rap": true,
        "rh": 0,
        "inputs": 0,
        "x": 190,
        "y": 400,
        "wires": [
            ["ec_json_parse"]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "ec_json_parse",
        "type": "json",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "Parse JSON",
        "property": "payload",
        "action": "",
        "pretty": false,
        "x": 430,
        "y": 400,
        "wires": [
            ["ec_format_state"]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "ec_format_state",
        "type": "function",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "Format State Change",
        "func": "var data = msg.payload;\nvar parts = msg.topic.split('/');\nvar entityType = parts[3] || 'unknown';\nvar slug = parts[4] || 'unknown';\n\nmsg.payload = {\n    entity: slug,\n    type: entityType,\n    state: data.current_state,\n    changed: data.changed_keys,\n    source: data.source || 'unknown'\n};\nreturn msg;",
        "outputs": 1,
        "timeout": "",
        "noerr": 0,
        "initialize": "",
        "finalize": "",
        "libs": [],
        "x": 640,
        "y": 400,
        "wires": [
            ["ec_debug_state"]
        ]
    },
    {
        "id": "ec_debug_state",
        "type": "debug",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "State Changed",
        "active": true,
        "tosidebar": true,
        "console": false,
        "tostatus": true,
        "complete": "payload",
        "targetType": "msg",
        "statusVal": "payload.entity",
        "statusType": "auto",
        "x": 850,
        "y": 400,
        "wires": []
    },
    {
        "id": "ec_comment",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "tab_entity_controller",
        "name": "How to use this flow",
        "info": "Control an entity's state via MQTT. Click an inject button to update the entity's state. The state manager subscribes to these MQTT topics and processes the update.\n\nPrerequisite: Create an entity with slug 'gallery-light-1' via the Fleet Manager API or Dashboard first.\n\n**Top row - State Updates (device -> Maestra):**\nPublishes to `maestra/entity/state/update/<slug>` with payload `{\"state\": {...}, \"source\": \"nodered\"}`.\nThe state manager merges this into the entity's current state (PATCH semantics).\nTo replace state entirely, change the topic to `maestra/entity/state/set/<slug>`.\n\n**Bottom row - State Broadcasts (Maestra -> devices):**\nListens on `maestra/entity/state/+/+` which matches `maestra/entity/state/<entity_type>/<slug>`.\nThese broadcasts fire whenever any entity's state changes, from any source (MQTT, HTTP API, NATS, OSC).\nThe payload includes: current_state, previous_state, changed_keys, source, and timestamp.\n\nTo target a specific entity, change the listener topic to `maestra/entity/state/+/gallery-light-1`.",
        "x": 160,
        "y": 60,
        "wires": []
    },

    {
        "id": "tab_event_logger",
        "type": "tab",
        "label": "Event Logger",
