    {
        "id": "sc_comment",
        "type": "comment",
        "z": "tab_show_control",
        "name": "Show Control Flow",
        "info": "This flow listens for show state changes via MQTT and routes them by phase.\n\nConnect your custom logic to the phase outputs:\n- PRE-SHOW: warm up lights, start ambient audio, calibrate sensors\n- ACTIVE: start main content, enable interactions\n- PAUSED: freeze current state, mute audio\n- SHUTDOWN: blackout lights, stop all outputs, prepare for power off\n\nShow phases: idle, pre_show, active, paused, post_show, shutdown\n\nTo trigger show transitions from Node-RED, use an MQTT out node:\n- Topic: maestra/show/command/go\n- Topic: maestra/show/command/pause\n- Topic: maestra/show/command/shutdown",
        "x": 170,
        "y": 100,
        "wires": []
    }
